				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing Plane of Fire? need guide please<a name="42388"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 26 04 2:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My bard is still too lil to go to the Table, or for that fact even flagged.  But I have been there many a nights with my wizard.  Getting to the table is fairly easy. If you are familiar with PoF, there is a Castle Wall with a rock out in front. With invis up (watching for see invis roamers) wait at the rock and watch the two roaming guards that see invis.  Once they cross or whatever and are out of range to the sides you can run right up the middle, staying inbetween the buildings. If you stay in the middle of the path between the buildings you should make it to the table no problem.
<br />

<br />
From what I have read and my exp with my bard. Most of your exp will be chant kiting the mobs around the table area. Unless you get in an agro kite group. We'd pull 4 with a druid and nuke the crap outta the mobs with 3-4 wizzies ussually.
<br />

<br />
Getting out just do the opposite, but you have to be carefull of the two roamers outside the wall. That or invest in some gate pots or do the gate neck quest.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
