				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing Plane of Fire? need guide please<a name="44332"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 5 04 2:01 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>tables is cake to solo ,ive never been an ae kiter though not sure if you could but probably ,i jus chant kite an drop an angstlichs on em every time it drops,with war drums and max instrument aas they drop reasonably fast ,189 a tick and four dots cos i bought the LDoN magic dot cos of course the Fire one doesnt stick . as for getting out well ..
<br />
1. gate ! gate neck is so valuable to bards its not funny ,or pottery and thurg potions .
<br />
2. OT hammer ! i mez and slow a mob haste myself and beat on it till i gate ,scary in fire but often the hammer procs first hit so hey ,an the yellow cons ther aint so scary ..
<br />
3. there is a Door in castle 1 ,if your coming back from tables its on your left on the ground floor where most groups usually camp ,load up Kazumis and your best Fire resists ,i can get 500 easy with amp vots PoV and abalone mask ,and dont forget the ever valuable SS bracer LOL . hit a fresh selos and lev yourself ,(once again singing steel is the win ) click the door open and run like h*ll ,dont stop to say hi to the half dozen blue Mephits that are eager to be your new friends ,instead boot it down the tunnel an take a running dive into the lava pool at the end ,remembering to Fade as you enter the lava ,and keeping fire resists up . staying to the top of the tunnel i find is best ,as it makes it easy to judge the slope etc and to see when you can get out ,use kazumis whenever you think you need to . when you get out you are in a shaft that goes up ,at first glance doesnt seem to be a way up but a part of the side is good enough to use as a ramp . i advise sitting and regenning before you head to the top as you are in a small cave with Mobs in it ,which is located on the island in the middle of the fire Lake ,once out fade again to blow off your new friends and easy as pie you can now get to the zone out .</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
